duplicates are present it returns\n            // the position of last element\n            while (mid+1<n && arr[mid+1] == key)\n                 mid++;\n            break;\n        }\n\n        //     "code": "/* Codeforces 1191B - Tokitsukaze and Mahjong*/\n\n#include <iostream>\n\n#define min(a, b) ((a > b) ? b : a)\n#define ROW 9\n#define COL 3\n\nstatic int cards[ROW][COL]; // Row from 1 - 9, Col represents m - p - s\nstatic short koutsu = 3; // Number of cards missing to form a koutsu\nstatic short shuntsu = 3; // Number of cards missing to form a shuntsu\n\nbool check_win(); // Check if this is currently a winning state\n\nint main()\n{\n    std::string s; // Iterator through the three cards\n    int index = 0;\n\n    while (index++ < 3 && std::cin >> s) // Place all the cards in their correct position\n    {\n        short rownum = s[0] - '0' - 1;\n        short colnum;\n\n        switch(s[1])\n        {\n        case 'm':\n            colnum = 0;\n            break;\n        case 'p':\n            colnum = 1;\n            break;\n        case 's':\n            colnum = 2;\n            break;\n        }\n\n        cards[rownum][colnum]++;\n    }\n\n    if (check_win())\n        std::cout << \"0\";\n\n    else\n    {\n        std::cout << min(koutsu, shuntsu);\n    }\n\n    return 0;\n}\n\n\nbool check_win()\n{\n    /* Check for a koutsu*/\n    for (short row = 0; row < ROW; row++)\n    {\n        for (short col = 0; col < COL; col++)\n        {\n            if (cards[row][col] == 3) // 3 identical cards forms a koutsu\n                return true;\n\n            else\n            {\n                koutsu = min(koutsu, 3 - cards[row][col]);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    /* Check for a shuntsu*/\n    for (short row = 0; row < ROW - 2; row++)\n    {\n        for (short col = 0; col < COL; col++)\n        {\n            if (cards[row][col] == cards[row + 1][col] &&\n                cards[row][col] == cards[row + 2][col] && cards[row][col] == 1)\n                    return true;\n\n            else\n            {\n                short missing = 0; // How many missing to form a shuntsu\n\n                for (short rowit = row; rowit < row + 3; rowit++)\n                {\n                    if (cards[rowit][col] == 0)\n                        missing++;\n                }\n\n                shuntsu = min(shuntsu, missing);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    return false;\n}\n",

    "code": "#################\n# July 17th 2019.\n#################\n\n##############################################################\n# Class Definition.\nclass Mahjong:\n    # Method to determine solution.\n    def requiredTileCount(self):\n        # Finding Costs and return minimum tiles.\n        mahjong.costOfMentsu();mahjong.costOfKoutsu()\n        return min(self.costM,self.costK)\n    # Method to determine cost of pursuing mentsu.\n    def costOfMentsu(self):\n        cost = 3\n        for suite in ['m','p','s']:\n            for digit in range(1,10):\n                cost = min(cost,3-self.tiles[suite][digit])\n        self.costM = cost\n    # Method to determine cost of pursuing koutsu.\n    def costOfKoutsu(self):\n        cost = 3\n        for suite in ['m','p','s']:\n            for index in range(1,8):\n                target = self.tiles[suite][index:index+3]\n                cost = min(cost,self.count_zeros(target))\n        self.costK = cost\n    # Method to count number of zeroes in a list.\n    def count_zeros(self,listy):\n        count = 0\n        for i in range(len(listy)):\n            if listy[i] == 0: count+=1\n        return count\n    # Constructor.\n    def __init__(self,hand):\n        # Getting Hand and setting up tile dictionary.\n        self.tiles = {}\n        for suite in ['m','p','s']:self.tiles[suite] = [0]*10\n        # Loading Hand into dictionary.\n        for index in [0,1,2]:\n            value,key = list(hand.pop(0))\n            # Adding to tiles.\n            self.tiles[key][int(value)]+=1\n        # For retaining final costs.\n        self.costM,self.costK = 3,3\n##############################################################\n# Making Mahjong instance.\nmahjong = Mahjong(list(input().split(' ')))\nprint(mahjong.requiredTileCount())\n##############################################################\n\n                      ########################################\n                      #
